  "text": "Key aspects are first to learn interesting skills which can be transferred between several tasks. These skills can be even more transferable if they are uncorrelated from the learned task [Heess et al., 2016] . Second, temporal abstraction of executed actions through acquired skills makes the learning process easier. Let's take, as an example, MuJoCo [CITATION_1] , which is a usually used environment in works related to skills. In this environment, the joints of the robot can be controlled by an agent to achieve, for example, locomotion tasks. The idea of some work is to generate skills like move forward or move backward with an intrinsic reward. These skills can then be used for a navigation task.",
